# AI / speech / meeting tools

Use when adding or changing: local LLM, **STT/ASR**, **speaker diarization**, **meeting minutes / clerk**, summarization, or related AI tools.

## Architecture fit (non-negotiable)

This site is **static GitHub Pages**. Default: **on-device / in-browser** processing.

| Approach | Allowed? |
|----------|----------|
| Transformers.js / ONNX / WASM / WebGPU in Worker | Yes (preferred) — mirror `LocalAI` |
| Web Speech API / MediaRecorder / Web Audio | Yes |
| Upload audio to a **user-chosen** remote API with explicit consent + local key storage | Only if user requests cloud; never hardcode secrets |
| New server/backend on this repo for inference | No (hosting is static) unless user explicitly migrates hosting |

## Suggested module layout for a new AI tool

```text
src/scripts/tools/<id>/
  types.ts              # TranscriptSegment, Speaker, MinutesDoc
  asr.ts                # STT/ASR adapter interface + impl
  diarization.ts        # speaker labels over time
  minutes.ts            # transcript → structured minutes
  storage.ts            # IndexedDB / Cache / optional FS Access
src/components/tools/<Name>.svelte
src/components/tools/<id>/worker.ts   # heavy model I/O
src/content/tool-docs/<id>.mdx
# wire component in src/pages/tools/[id]/index.astro with client:only="svelte"
```

## Adapter interfaces (prefer functions + types)

```ts
export type TranscriptSegment = {
  startMs: number;
  endMs: number;
  text: string;
  speakerId?: string;
  confidence?: number;
};

export type AsrAdapter = {
  id: string;
  transcribe(input: Blob | Float32Array, opts?: { language?: string }): Promise<TranscriptSegment[]>;
};

export type DiarizationAdapter = {
  id: string;
  diarize(audio: Blob, transcript?: TranscriptSegment[]): Promise<TranscriptSegment[]>;
};

export type MinutesResult = {
  title: string;
  attendees: string[];
  agenda: string[];
  decisions: string[];
  actionItems: { owner?: string; task: string; due?: string }[];
  summary: string;
  rawTranscript: TranscriptSegment[];
};
```

Keep UI free of model details; swap adapters without rewriting the Svelte shell.

## UX / privacy / security requirements

- State clearly: **audio/transcript stays in the browser** (unless user opts into a cloud provider).
- Ask mic permission only on user gesture; handle deny/AbortError gracefully.
- Show load progress for model downloads (LocalAI pattern).
- Cache models via Cache Storage or optional directory picker (`showDirectoryPicker`).
- Provide export: Markdown / JSON download; optional copy button.
- Never log raw audio/transcripts to analytics or `console` in prod paths.
- For minutes: show editable draft before “final”; label AI-generated content.
- Validate uploaded audio: MIME allowlist + max size; reject exotic containers early.
- Do not render transcript text with `{@html}` / `innerHTML` (XSS) — use text nodes.
- Cross-check `security-anti-patterns.mdc` + `privacy-third-parties.mdc` on every AI tool PR.

## Performance

- Run inference in a **Worker**; stream partial transcripts to UI via `postMessage`.
- Prefer quantized ONNX / small models suitable for browser.
- Support cancel/abort mid-run; terminate Worker on destroy.
- Gate WebGPU with capability check + WASM CPU fallback.

## Testing

- Unit-test pure formatters (`minutes.ts` merging, timestamp formatting) in `tests/tools-*.test.ts`.
- Playwright: fake media flags already in `playwright.config.ts`; mock Worker messages where models are too heavy for CI.
- Do not download multi‑GB models in CI; use fixtures / stub adapters in tests.

## Dependencies

Prefer extending existing `@huggingface/transformers` before adding overlapping stacks. Justify any new heavy dependency in the PR/summary.
